*******************************************************************************
       Name: Momentum Drain
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_CHAR_OFFENSIVE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 100
 Wait Beats: 12
 Can Learn: TRUE
Noun Damage: momentum drain
   Wear-Off: Your momentum returns to normal.
Acquisition:
   - Kinetimancer: level 5
Description:
   Momentum Drain redirects the target's combat momentum, applying hitroll
   and damroll penalties that represent their force being siphoned away.
   This reflects the Kinetic Formulists' momentum doctrine: "rather than
   generating force from nothing, the practitioner identifies existing
   force vectors and redirects them."

   Duration: 3 + (Kinetimancer level / 5) rounds
   Hitroll penalty: -(Kinetimancer level * 2 + Necromancer level
                      + Egomancer level)
   Damroll penalty: same as hitroll
   Mana cost: 100

   Refocused from mana-drain (which overlaps with existing Mana Drain
   spell accessible via Necromancer/Egomancer prereqs) to combat-stat
   drain, which better represents the momentum-redirection lore.
*******************************************************************************
